hdr128106-bc.def: The mandatory minimum number of calendar days that legally must be paid by the government, the employer or both. It refers to leave related to the birth of a child that is available only to the mother; it does not cover parental leave that is available to both parents.

hdr128106-bc.source: World Bank (2020b). Gender Statistics database. Washington, DC. http://data.worldbank.org. Accessed 21 July 2020.

hdr136906-bc.source: HDRO calculations based on data from UNDESA (2019a), UNESCO Institute for Statistics (2020), Barro and Lee (2018), World Bank (2020a), ILO (2020) and IMF (2020).
